        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 2 at 3:28PM EDT until May 2 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 328 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles south of
Cadiz, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
St. Clairsville, Flushing, Adena, Holloway, New Athens and
Harrisville.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm is capable of producing
dangerous hail.</instruction>
